name: Hand Grip
description: A handgrip exercise is a small device that aims to strengthen a lifterâ€™s grip and forearm strength. The operation of a hand grip exerciser is quite simple.

name: Yoga
description: Although yoga classes do require yoga mats, they are not the only places where yoga mats can be found. Most gyms house mats of this kind in warm-up areas in order to provide this soft surface for the lifter to exercise on.

name: Push up
description: Push up bars are curved metal or plastic bars that allow lifters to perform the pushup movement without putting excessive pressure on the wrists.

name: Barbell Rack
description: A barbell rack is a large stationary piece of architecture that is required when performing many exercises. Usually standing 8 to 12 ft tall, barbell racks allow a lifter the optimal place to pick up and place down the weight.

name: Dumbbell
description: An adjustable dumbbell system (ADS) is a single dumbbell, about 12-18 inches wide, that gives the lifter the ability to rotate or change the weight in 2.5 pound increments.

name: Bench Press
description: A bench press is a large piece of equipment that encompasses a lifting bench, small barbell rack, and barbell. The bench press system works together to allow the lifter to complete a number of pressing movements.

name: Air Resistance Bike
description: An air resistance bike is a piece of equipment that mimics the actions and muscle activation involved in riding a bike. The machine operates much like a bike itself, with small pedals for your feet, and handles up top to hold on to.

name: Treadmill
description: The treadmill is the most popular piece of gym equipment usd to improve cardiovascular endurance. Treadmills are very customizable, allowing users to speed or or slow the moving platform however they please.

name: Glute Ham Developer
description: The glute ham developer is a piece of gym equipment used to train the glutes and hamstrings together. To use it, the athlete will lay facing down with their quads on a padded bar with their feet strapped in place.
